`mmap` / `munmap` methods on `ClientRegions` (after `set_brk`, before the closing `}` at line 122):

```rust
    /// Allocate an anonymous mmap region of `len` bytes. `len` is rounded up to
    /// a page; the base address is bump-allocated from `mmap_next`. Returns the
    /// chosen base. Errors: `EINVAL` if `len` is 0 or rounding/bumping would
    /// overflow `u64`; `ENOMEM` if no region slot is free.
    fn mmap(&mut self, len: u64) -> Result<u64, i32> {
        if len == 0 {
            return Err(EINVAL);
        }
        let size = len
            .checked_add(PAGE_SIZE - 1)
            .map(|v| v & !(PAGE_SIZE - 1))
            .ok_or(EINVAL)?;

        let start = self.mmap_next;
        let end = start.checked_add(size).ok_or(EINVAL)?;

        for r in self.regions.iter_mut() {
            if r.kind == Kind::Unused {
                *r = Region {
                    start,
                    end,
                    kind: Kind::Mmap,
                };
                self.mmap_next = end;
                return Ok(start);
            }
        }
        Err(ENOMEM)
    }

    /// Unmap the `Mmap` region based at `addr`. Returns the page-aligned
    /// `[start, end)` the caller must sweep with `VMCTL_PT_UNMAP`, and marks the
    /// region `Unused`. `EINVAL` if no `Mmap` region starts at `addr`. `len` is
    /// page-aligned-up for the returned end but the match is keyed on the region
    /// base, so an over- or under-stated `len` cannot unmap a neighbor.
    fn munmap(&mut self, addr: u64, len: u64) -> Result<(u64, u64), i32> {
        let size = len
            .checked_add(PAGE_SIZE - 1)
            .map(|v| v & !(PAGE_SIZE - 1))
            .ok_or(EINVAL)?;
        let end = addr.checked_add(size).ok_or(EINVAL)?;

        for r in self.regions.iter_mut() {
            if r.kind == Kind::Mmap && r.start == addr {
                // Sweep no further than the region actually covers, even if the
                // caller passed a larger len.
                let sweep_end = end.min(r.end);
                *r = Region::EMPTY;
                return Ok((addr, sweep_end));
            }
        }
        Err(EINVAL)
    }
```

